{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01J3Pe6DwyGkx4icE5E1gk6p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Elections are now stable.\n\n**What was wrong:** The `rs0` replica set had only two voting, data-bearing members (`mongo-rs-0`, `mongo-rs-1`) — an even vote count, which causes election instability (no majority can be formed if one member is unreachable). A `mongo-arb-0` arbiter pod was already running with `--replSet rs0` but had never been added to the config (`NotYetInitialized`).\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Set a cluster-wide default write concern (`w:\"majority\"`) — required because MongoDB 6.0 blocks adding an arbiter (PSS→PSA) that would change the implicit default write concern.\n2. `rs.addArb(\"mongo-arb-0.mongo-arb.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\")` — added the existing arbiter pod as a voting, `arbiterOnly` member.\n\n**Result:**\n- Voting members now 3 (odd) → stable elections: `mongo-rs-0` PRIMARY, `mongo-rs-1` SECONDARY, `mongo-arb-0` ARBITER, all `health:1`.\n- The arbiter holds **no data** (`arbiterOnly:true`), so no storage cost was added and no data-bearing member was introduced.\n- App database intact: `app.test` still has 3 documents (unchanged before/after)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":746,"cache_read_input_tokens":33371,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":746},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d3d1fd99-b68c-4026-8452-c79af644c550","uuid":"386e7d19-ab53-489a-a175-b3a6271f7649","request_id":"req_011CcAPcrHBpypbRoqVZ1v9t"}
